Politicians and media personalities have honoured ANC struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada who passed away following brain surgery.Neeshan Balton, Executive Director of the Ahmed Kathrada Foundation, said the anti-apartheid struggle veteran breathed his last today .Balton added: This is great loss to the ANC, the broader liberation movement and South Africa as a whole. Internationally, he was staunch in his support for the Palestinian struggle. Kathy was an inspiration to millions in different parts of the world .To Ntate #AhmedKathrada, your life was spent in the fight for our freedom. May your soul rest in revolutionary peace #RIP pic.twitter.com/CmaFBcxD5Y&mdash; RSA Min of Sport (@MbalulaFikile) March 28, 2017The Progressive Professionals Forum @PPF_SA mourns the passing on of this icon of the struggle. Condolences to the family. #RIPKathrada pic.twitter.com/Ad1mXLIBpL&mdash; Mzwanele Manyi (@MzwaneleManyi) March 28, 2017Take your final salute cde Kathy. You have served South Africa well. Have a deserved rest. It is for the rest to serve South Africa well.&mdash; Vusi Pikoli (@VusiPikoli) March 28, 2017Words can&#39;t describe the loss to the country with the loss of Ahmed Kathrada. No point mourning. Let&#39;s celebrate and emulate his life&mdash; Mbhazima Shilowa (@Enghumbhini) March 28, 2017#Kathrada &quot;We belong to Allah and to Him we shall return.&quot; #UncleKathy served with dedication and he will always be remembered. pic.twitter.com/c0jnrzCt5t&mdash; Yusuf Abramjee (@Abramjee) March 28, 2017RIP Ahmed Kathrada, thank you for your service and example, we stand on the shoulders of giants.&mdash; John Steenhuisen MP (@jsteenhuisen) March 28, 2017My deep condolences to #AhmedKathrada family, his political party and the people of SA. We have indeed lost a giant, iQhawe. Lala Ngoxolo.&mdash; Mmusi Maimane (@MmusiMaimane) March 28, 2017 Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za